      ArkCase implements anonymous case-by-number lookup through a Spring
      service (`GetCaseByNumberService.getCaseByNumber(String caseNumber)`)
      that delegates to a JPA DAO method (`findByCaseNumber`). The portal
      gateway (`PortalRequestService.getRequestStatus(...)`) wraps that
      lookup for unauthenticated callers and returns a `PortalResponse`. The
      ServiceNow target collapses both surfaces into a single anonymous
      Service Portal page (THIS file) that embeds a widget that GETs from a
      scripted REST endpoint - no Spring beans, no JPA DAO, no
      `PortalRequestService`. The Java code's `getCaseByNumber()` and
      `getRequestStatus()` map semantically to the
      page->widget->REST->Script-Include->GlideRecord chain triggered by
      THIS page's lookup widget, with the additional response-shape
      whitelisting (status, subject, opened_date only) enforced server-side
      by the Script Include.

